<& /page/page_title.mas, title=>"Genomes of <i>Solanum lycopersicum</i> inbred lines" &>

<div class="page_introduction">
  The genomes of tomato inbred lines consist mostly of <a href="/organism/1/view/"><i>Solanum lycopersicum</i></a>
  and carry genome fragments originating from various tomato wild species.
  Breeders develop inbreds for introducing valuable genetic variation from multiple wild species and/or accessions while maintaining
  a genetic background of the domesticated species. This is achieved by outcrossing followed by multiple genetrations of backcrossing and selection.

</div>


<&| /page/info_section.mas, title => 'Gh13 genome' &>
  Gh13 is a begomovirus resistant line carrying the <a href="/locus/8216/view"><i>Ty3</i></a> gene.
  This line was developed in Guatamala <a href="/publication/18734/view">(Mejia et al., 2004)</a>
  were it has been tested over multiple seasons and consistently shows very good resistance against high begomovirus pressure there. Resistance in Gh13 is reportedly derived from <a href="/organism/938/view"><i>S. habrochaites</i></a>  <a href="/publication/18735/view">(Vidavsky and Czosnek, 1998)</a><br />

