<&| /page/info_section.mas, title => 'BTI87 genome' &>
  BTI87 is a begomovirus resistant line carrying the <a href="/locus/8216/view"><i>Ty3</i></a> gene.
  BTI87 was developed in Guatemala and maintains a high level of resistance derived from the begomovirus-resistant inbred Gc171, which is in turn derived from <a href="/organism/1373/view"><i>S. chilense</i> accession <a href="/stock/28625/view">LA1932</a> <a href="/publication/18736/view">(Scott and Schuster, 2007)</a><br />

