<&| /page/info_section.mas, title => 'Fla630 genome' &>
  Fla630 is a  Fusarium Wilt Race 3 resistant tomato inbred line carrying the <a href="/locus/718/view"><i>I-3</i></a> gene.
   The I-3 gene was introgressed from <a href="/organism/19/view"><i>S. pennellii</i> and confers resistance to race 3. Although I-3 provides effective control, it is negatively associated with several horticultural traits, including increased sensitivity to bacterial spot disease (Xanthomonas spp.)<br />

